snippet: With roughly 990,000 votes counted, Washington residents appeared to reject mandatory labeling of genetically engineered products.
abstract: Some of nation's major food companies declare victory over initiative in Washington State that would have required labeling of some foods that contain biotech ingredients, though supporters of labeling hold out hope that hundreds of thousands of uncounted votes might yet turn the tide.
lead_paragraph: With roughly 990,000 votes counted, Washington residents appeared to reject mandatory labeling of genetically engineered products.

headline.main: Food Companies Claim Victory Against Labeling Initiative in Washington State
headline.print_headline: Food Companies Claim Victory Against Labeling Initiative in Washington State
